NOTE After loading data and performing few basic steps I did grid search on various parameters of SVC. The output showed me the rbf kernal. thus telling me it is a non linear problem also with the help of pairplot I got to know the distribution is not Normal distribution thus algo like Naive Bayes and Log Regression wont work.

**STEPS FOR THIS PROJECT:

  1. Iteration 1: Consists of Descrptive analysis, multivariate analysis, Outliers and missing value detection, splitind data to X and Y , splitting Train and Test data to 70:30, data preprocessing(scaling data) and normal various model building to get genral idea and accuracy.

  2. Iteration 2: Here I cleaned outliers from cmapaign,balance and age column and dropped column such as pdays and previous column. Column such as days and duration are untouched as they dont have outliers and are highly important to target column. Then based on new data I evaluated the models again. Depending on their score, size of data and the problem I faced with each algorithm. I decided to choose model best form ensemble tech i.e Decision Tree.

  3. Grid Search and Cross validation : I performed this on Decision tree and SVM (reason as stated above in NOTE) to get optimal parameter. On decision tree I performed cross validation and achieved a good score . So this step is my regularization step.

  4. Ensemble tech: I performed bagging, Boosting(adaboost and gradient boost), random forest also Xtreme Forests on Decision tree. I performed grid search only on randomforest to tune hyperparameters. I have also done cross validation in ever techniques stated above and printed cv average and cv std deviation

  5. Ensemble tech advance: I have tried to make stacking model and voting classifier model which include various model. NOTE: This is just to see and know concept better

  6. Conclusion for final model that I would be selecting for production.

NOTE. For 95% of confidence interval I have attach 2 pictures with name '1' and '2'. Pictures explain what approach I took to calculate the range. Also I have found range for each algorithem from Iteration 2 SVM to Voting Classifier. The approach I took was told in the stats module week 2.

Further each important information is provided in each cell. information such as why I dropped pdays and previous is provided down the line

I perform grid search on SVM with different kernal. The output came was RBF which is a non linear kernal so therefore the problem is non linear¶

2. Iteration2¶

  • I have cleaned the data as much as possible. I have cleaned data such that the new dataset mentains it meaning as per old dataset. For this I have removed outliers which is the best approach I have taken as told during my learning period
  • Here I removed outliers from campaign balance and the from age column I have set the threshold of 68.
  • I decided to drop previous as it had only less number of valid region aslo its corr() is very very less and after removing it outliers I found out its max and min value which 0 in both cases
  • I decided to drop pdays reason stated in IN [71], In[72] and In [19]
  • I prepared model, based on new data and concluded my final model which is Decision tree
  • I could also replace outliers with median of that column but in doing so I would be manipulating data to a very large extent as outliers are very large

NOTE : This step (Iteration 2) is performed many number of times to get best results
